issue.title: Add portable flag to store config in app directory
issue.body:
Redirects the config files to the app directory when the `--portable` flag is passed at runtime.

This has been requested informally a couple of times in Discord - if there's a formal feature request issue I could not find it but I would be glad to link to it.

I took a very simple approach to make this work. If there's a more preferable way to handle bool for the portable state I would be glad to modify it.

comment.body: Looks good! I haven't done a proper review yet, but I noticed there are no tests. I'm not sure how we could do a proper end to end test, but at least we can test the isPortable flag. Could you add a test for that? And maybe you have an idea how we can test that the flag gets set if you pass the parameter, too?

commits.message:
Allow some floating point error when intersecting ray and triangle

I don't know why this is now necessary, but we had some tests failing
on Xcode15 (CI was fine). I assume that something changed about how
AppleClang does floating point arithmetic, even though I can't find any
info on this. Anyway - allowing more floating point error works and
the tests are now fine.

Change an expectation that relies on floating point serialization

I think this is necessary because of some change in how clang treats
floating point numbers - leading to minor differences in accuracies.

Merge pull request #4356 from TrenchBroom/fix-xcode15-bugs

Fix some problems when using Xcode 15
